# Commit Message Types

## Description
Defines the allowed types for commit messages.

## Rule
The commit type must be one of the following:
- `feat`: A new feature
- `fix`: A bug fix
- `test`: Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
- `chore`: Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools and libraries
- `refactor`: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature

## Examples
✅ Valid:
```
feat(ABC-123): ✨ Add new feature
fix(XYZ-987): 🐛 Fix bug
test(QWE-456): ✅ Add tests
chore(DEV-100): 🔧 Update dependencies
refactor(OPS-321): ♻️ Improve code structure
```

❌ Invalid:
```
feature(ABC-123): ✨ Add new feature
bugfix(XYZ-987): 🐛 Fix bug
update(DEV-100): 🔧 Update dependencies
```

## Notes
- Type must be lowercase
- Must be one of the predefined types
- Cannot be abbreviated or modified
